      "title": "Possessive",
      "subtitle": "Il-possessiv — using ta' and tiegħi/tiegħek/etc",
      "intro": "To say 'someone's something' in Maltese, use the small word ta' (of). 'Sara's dog' becomes 'the dog of Sara'.",
      "examples": [
        {"phrase": "Il-kelb ta' Sara", "en": "Sara's dog"},
        {"phrase": "Id-dar ta' Tom", "en": "Tom's house"},
        {"phrase": "Il-karozza tal-missier", "en": "Father's car"},
        {"phrase": "Il-ġuvni ta' Marta", "en": "Marta's boyfriend"},
        {"phrase": "Il-villa tan-nanna", "en": "Grandmother's villa"},
        {"phrase": "Il-pjanti taz-zija", "en": "Aunt's plants"}
      ],
